issue.title: proxy method provided has Undici connection can\'t work with proxies error
issue.body:
It's not uncommon that somebody already opened an issue or in the best case it's already fixed but not merged. That's the reason why you should [search](https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch-js/issues) at first before submitting a new one.

**Please read this entire template before posting any issue. If you ignore these instructions
and post an issue here that does not follow the instructions, your issue might be closed,
locked, and assigned the `not reproducible` label.**

## 🐛 Bug Report

According to your documentation, i can simply provide an "proxy" key to the client object, but it always gives the Undici connection can\'t work with proxies.

## To Reproduce

Steps to reproduce the behavior:

Paste your code here:

```js
const client = new Client({
    node:'mynode',
    auth: {
        username: 'myname',
        password: 'mypassword'
      },
    proxy:'http://myproxy:myport'

```

<!--
In some cases, it might be challenging to reproduce the bug in a few lines of code.
You can fork the following repository, which contains all the configuration needed
to spin up a three nodes Elasticsearch cluster with security enabled.
The repository also contains a preconfigured client instance that you can use to reproduce the issue.
https://github.com/delvedor/es-reproduce-issue
--->

## Expected behavior

A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen.

Paste the results here:

```js
ConfigurationError: Undici connection agent options can't be a function or a boolean


```

## Your Environment

- *node version*: 14.19
- `@elastic/elasticsearch` *version*: >=8.5.0
- *os*: Windows
- *any other relevant information*

comment.body: [Proxy connection docs](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/client/javascript-api/current/client-connecting.html#client-connect-proxy) now include a note about using `HttpConnection` in 8.0+ when you need to configure a proxy.
